commit.message:
Bump version, add a check and a control for visibility

Add a check so cmsCreatedExtendedTransform behaves like other transform generators
Add a #define symbol to control visibility in linux. Useful if you want to create a so that contains lcms as static library.
Bump version number

Fix a inconsistence introduced in latest commit

Size of parameter may differ on several compilers

Delete testbed.exp

delete spare file

Fix: Color management on blocks > 4Gb fail

Fix an error on huge memory blocks. size_t is part of C99

Remove duplicate check

A typo or a bad merge... thanks to Robin Watts for pointing out.

Set the min/max conditions

TAC below 1% makes no sense at all

clean PS error path

Fix a theoretical leak when recovering from error
Merge branch 'master' of https://github.com/mm2/Little-CMS

Minor cosmetic

Some minor changes that does not affect normal workflow

commit.message:
Fix a groff warning about the missing "p" macro.

Patch courtesy of Florian Ernst <florian@debian.org>

Run tests in the build directory

Test data files are copied into the build directory so that the tests can run
there instead of creating new files (e.g. new.icc) in the source directory

Bump minimum meson version to 0.64, because we are using fs.copyfile().
